article.description: — Javon Freeman-Liberty had 26 points as DePaul got past Marquette 91-80 on Wednesday night.
article.headline: Freeman-Liberty carries DePaul past Marquette 91-80
article.story: CHICAGO -- — Javon Freeman-Liberty had 26 points as DePaul got past Marquette 91-80 on Wednesday night. David Jones had 16 points for DePaul (15-14, 6-13 Big East Conference). Jalen Terry added 16 points and eight rebounds. Brandon Johnson had 13 points. Justin Lewis had 26 points and 10 rebounds for the Golden Eagles (18-11, 10-8). Stevie Mitchell and Darryl Morsell added 12 points apiece. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/hub/college-basketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
